<br>
Where clerics rule the AA world is quite simply in the archetype category.  Unless you really want to be an Archon or whatever just pop points into these abilties with the exception of the must have Mass Group Buff.<br>
<br>
I'll use 3 different clerics to discuss 3 different routes we took and why: Jherek, Penrif, Rundo<br>
<br>
Jherek: Jherek took the most classical approach to cleric AA's going for mana and healing abilities first.  After run 3 and something else 3 (here i'd recommend either regen 3 or stamina 3) he moved onto SCM 3, Healing Gift 3, got MGB, Celestial Regeneration, and Divine Resurrection, went on to do the PoP wisdom abilities, and I believe now is looking to do SCR followed by SCRM...<br>
<br>
Penrif: Penrif is a nutball and likes to nuke so if you are like him your AA will look more like:<br>
general stuff as above, SCM 3, MGB, Healing Gift 2, SCF 2, MC 2, Divine Arb (very useful I hear), Unfailing Divinity 3, etc.<br>
<br>
Rundo: Rundo is what we'd like to call a wanna be tank cleric <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Fortunately clerics have many AA to help with combat skills<br>
general stuff as above, SCM 3, MGB, Unfailing Divinity 1, ND 2, CA 1...will move on to ND 3, then CA 3, then LR 5, then CS 3, then ID 5 then SCF 3 (for procs) ... all combat skillz all the time<br>
<br>
Other good AA abilities not mentioned above include Radiant Cure (very useful I hear) and Bestow Divine Aura (limited in use but can be useful)<br>
<br>
Pretty much do what you want but I wouldn't hinge around getting AA for wisdom, do that with your gear...same with mana regen...use AA to either get you new abilities or make yourself more customized as a nuker, tank, or healer as needed.  MC 3 isn't a waste I'd say since it stacks with worn regen...however it also shouldn't be a priority at 6 AA point cost <p>Venerable Rundo Nundodundo<br>
Lvl 65 Ghetto Cleric Tank of Resolution<br>
<br>
37 AAs and counting...<br>
