&quot;You can take the dwarf out of the ghetto but you can't take the ghetto out of the dwarf&quot;-Nothsa</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jeninaicemyst>Jenina Icemyst</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(4/5/03 8:08:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=89.topic&index=10>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Cleric Alternate Advancement discussion</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Other good AA abilities not mentioned above include Radiant Cure (very useful I hear) and Bestow Divine Aura (limited in use but can be useful)<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Didn't mention radiant cure or divine arbitration because those are PoP abilities that require level 61.  Both are wonderful though - I would suggest getting div arb 1 first thing after dinging 61 and then radiant cure 1 then div arb 2 and 3 as soon as you get the levels for them.  I'm pretty happy with radiant cure 1 - I'll probably get levels 2 and 3 eventually but level one cures a lot already and I can pull out a clicky cure earring (or pure blood now) if it isn't enough.<br>
<br>
In my opinion the best cleric AAs are tied between spell casting mastery and divine arbitration.  Those two are must haves for every cleric.   <p>[65 Archon] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=231627">Ariene</a> (High Elf) Bristlebane<BR>
